#13315
Underground Sewers~
To the south you can see a bit of light, denoting the way back up to the
town.  Here the air is stale, not many seem to venture down here, not
a lot of the time anyways.  It is damp and a cold wind blows from somewhere
you can't figure, making a loud noise as it winds towards you, and is
evidence that a way out is nearby.  Off to the northeast/southeast is the
culd-de-sac, a good place to begin at.
~
