#13319
Culdesac, u-turn~
This is the opposite end of the entrance/exit room of the catacombs.  Thus
going northwest or southwest doesn't really matter unless you're interest in
going clockwise or counter-clockwise.  You notice the air here however is worse
then far west, basically to the point where it reeks, it's almost unbeareable.
The most obvious looking source seems to be a large grate on the lower east
wall, large enough for a body to fit through without too much trouble.
~
